Not sure what you mean by &#39;level&#39; -- there is no &#39;level&#39; property of a 
CrawlURI.

If by chance you mean a count of how many outlink-hops have been 
traveled since the seed, you can look the TooManyHopsDecideRule to see 
how that number is deduced -- by looking at the &#39;pathFromSeed&#39; string of 
one-character-per-hop. (You can see two other similar calculations in 
CrawlURI.getLinkHopCount() or CrawlURI.getEmbedHopCount().) You could 
alter &#39;pathFromSeed&#39; to cause different numbers to be calculated for 
these hop-counts.

(You could also add your own &#39;level&#39; property for your own purposes -- 
using the getData() Map in CrawlURI.)

- Gordon @ IA

